00:08:40.909 --> 00:08:42.009
4.

00:08:42.009 --> 00:08:46.950
America Has More Self-Identified Patriots
than Anywhere Else on Earth

00:08:46.950 --> 00:08:51.449
In July 2016, Gallup released the results
of their yearly patriotism poll.

00:08:51.449 --> 00:08:57.339
They found 52% of Americans call themselves
“extremely patriotic”, the lowest level

00:08:57.339 --> 00:08:58.980
in polling history.

00:08:58.980 --> 00:09:02.899
The news triggered a slew of introspective
articles by American writers, wondering what

00:09:02.899 --> 00:09:04.120
had gone wrong.

00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:08.040
For those reading elsewhere in the world,
it felt like stepping through the looking

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:09.040
glass.

00:09:09.040 --> 00:09:14.399
52% is such a good score it leaves other countries
eating the USA’s dust.

00:09:14.399 --> 00:09:18.110
Such levels of patriotism simply don’t exist
in the rest of the developed world.

00:09:18.110 --> 00:09:22.930
In a similar survey by YouGov, only 13% of
Brits thought their country was “the best

00:09:22.930 --> 00:09:24.110
in the world.”

00:09:24.110 --> 00:09:26.640
That was the highest score in the EU.

00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:29.500
Germany and France got only 5% each.

00:09:29.500 --> 00:09:34.509
The second and third highest-ranking countries
globally, India and Australia, scored 34%

00:09:34.509 --> 00:09:35.509
and 36%.

00:09:35.509 --> 00:09:38.000
But the US?

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:42.900
The US busted through the 40% mark, with an
additional 32% claiming America was at the

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:45.759
very least “better than most other countries.”

00:09:45.759 --> 00:09:50.110
For the majority of foreigners, the idea of
showing US-levels of patriotism is simply

00:09:50.110 --> 00:09:51.130
alien.

00:09:51.130 --> 00:09:54.550
You will never see a flag in every yard in
any other country on Earth.

00:09:54.550 --> 00:09:58.420
But that’s the US public for you: optimistic
to a tee.

00:09:58.420 --> 00:10:02.130
Even if they’re unhappy with their current
government, folks still believe that the idea

00:10:02.130 --> 00:10:04.420
of America itself is worth believing in.

00:10:04.420 --> 00:10:06.290
3.

00:10:06.290 --> 00:10:10.370
Americans are More Likely to Get Bitten by
Other Americans than Rats

00:10:10.370 --> 00:10:15.500
The stereotype is that Americans likes three
things: football, fast food, and violence

00:10:15.500 --> 00:10:16.699
(often all at once).

00:10:16.699 --> 00:10:19.410
It’s true that America’s murder rate is
crazy-high.

00:10:19.410 --> 00:10:23.399
It’s also true that the national sport is
getting drunk and starting bar-fights.

00:10:23.399 --> 00:10:27.009
But surely it’s not as bad as all that?

00:10:27.009 --> 00:10:32.350
Well, we hate to break it to you, but this
arresting statistic says otherwise.

00:10:32.350 --> 00:10:36.360
If you live in America, you are more likely
to be bitten by another American than you

00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:37.880
are by a rat.

00:10:37.880 --> 00:10:42.149
To be clear, this isn’t because US rats
are particularly docile or rare on the ground.

00:10:42.149 --> 00:10:46.579
Cities like New York are completely infested,
and people get bitten all the freakin’ time.

00:10:46.579 --> 00:10:51.490
There are over 40,000 rat bites recorded in
America each year.

00:10:51.490 --> 00:10:56.569
The only trouble is, there are at least 45,000
human bites recorded right alongside them.

00:10:56.569 --> 00:10:59.019
Again, this is a freaky fact for Americans,
too.

00:10:59.019 --> 00:11:03.100
But, also again, it’s just something that
doesn’t happen in most other countries.

00:11:03.100 --> 00:11:07.579
Sure, drunks in Britain like to hit each other,
and Italian soccer hooligans are violent as

00:11:07.579 --> 00:11:10.819
heck, but biting enough people to outstrip
rats?

00:11:10.819 --> 00:11:14.550
It’s something we can’t imagine happening
anywhere else.

00:11:14.550 --> 00:11:15.550
2.

00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:18.480
Americans Take ‘Fast Food’ Extremely Literally

00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:21.090
The US is the birthplace of fast food.

00:11:21.090 --> 00:11:24.790
It’s the nation that brought the world the
drive-thru, perfected the snack, and coined

00:11:24.790 --> 00:11:27.290
the phrase “lunch is for wimps.”

00:11:27.290 --> 00:11:29.260
Foreigners know all this intellectually.

00:11:29.260 --> 00:11:34.390
But confront them with a statistic like the
following, and it’ll still blow their minds.

00:11:34.390 --> 00:11:37.949
Americans, you see, are the 3rd fastest eaters
on Earth.

00:11:37.949 --> 00:11:43.339
On an average day, Americans spend only 74
minutes eating, nearly the lowest in the world.

00:11:43.339 --> 00:11:47.260
That’s only slightly over 20 minutes each
for breakfast, lunch and dinner, and far less

00:11:47.260 --> 00:11:50.040
if you include time put aside for eating snacks.

00:11:50.040 --> 00:11:53.740
If you live in the USA, this probably doesn’t
seem so weird to you (the working lunch is

00:11:53.740 --> 00:11:57.860
an American specialty), but if you live elsewhere…
man, you’re probably wondering how the heck

00:11:57.860 --> 00:11:58.860
they do it.

00:11:58.860 --> 00:12:01.870
In France, the average eating time is 135
minutes a day.

00:12:01.870 --> 00:12:04.180
In Turkey, it’s 162 minutes.

00:12:04.180 --> 00:12:08.450
Even in Japan, where people work far longer
hours than in the US, they still manage to

00:12:08.450 --> 00:12:11.379
put aside 117 minutes a day for chow.

00:12:11.379 --> 00:12:16.380
The only other countries to spend as little
time eating are Canada (72 minutes) and Mexico

00:12:16.380 --> 00:12:18.019
(under 70 minutes).

00:12:18.019 --> 00:12:22.740
This is probably to do with both the American
hard work ethic and fast food culture, which

00:12:22.740 --> 00:12:25.980
prioritizes productivity over relaxation.

00:12:25.980 --> 00:12:29.579
The same can be seen in a related statistic
on cooking times.

00:12:29.579 --> 00:12:35.019
Nowhere else on Earth do people spend as little
time cooking each day as in America.

