00:12:36.069 --> 00:12:40.069
Government Departments Have Official Advice
for Reporting Elvis Sightings

00:12:40.069 --> 00:12:44.540
One of the things foreigners know about the
US is that it’s full of wackos seeing wacko

00:12:44.540 --> 00:12:45.540
things.

00:12:45.540 --> 00:12:48.150
There’s a reason The X-Files was so popular
20 years ago.

00:12:48.150 --> 00:12:51.960
But it’s one thing to hear about guys filming
shaky footage of Bigfoot on their cell phone.

00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:56.790
It’s another entirely to hear that actual
US government departments have official advice

00:12:56.790 --> 00:12:58.120
for reporting Elvis sightings.

00:12:58.120 --> 00:13:01.459
Here, for example, is a link to the Federal
government’s official website for copyright.

00:13:01.459 --> 00:13:02.459
Hover your mouse over the link.

00:13:02.459 --> 00:13:03.459
See that it ends .gov?

00:13:03.459 --> 00:13:04.459
It’s impossible for anyone not representing
a government entity to register a .gov address.

00:13:04.459 --> 00:13:05.459
This site is legit.

00:13:05.459 --> 00:13:06.459
It’s part of the Federal government, and
paid for by taxpayers’ money.

00:13:06.459 --> 00:13:08.970
And it includes official advice on how to
copyright your sighting of Elvis.

00:13:08.970 --> 00:13:13.560
This isn’t a joke section put up by some
lighthearted bureaucrat indulging a whim.

00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:16.540
It’s completely, mind-bogglingly serious.

00:13:16.540 --> 00:13:21.110
Which means the government was getting deluged
with enough requests about Elvis sightings

00:13:21.110 --> 00:13:25.329
that they went to the trouble to post official
advice about it.

00:13:25.329 --> 00:13:36.899
OK, say it with me now, altogether: only in
America.

